In [17]:
def get_data_range():
    for i in range(10,P,10):
        sP = int(i)
        small_data = {'P':sP,
            'M':M,
            'rate_prior': 1,
            'metabolite_mask':met_mask[:sP,:],
            'y':y,
            'tiny':1e-8}
        yield small_data
    small_data = {'P':P,
            'M':M,
            'rate_prior': 1,
            'metabolite_mask':met_mask,
            'y':y,
            'tiny':1e-8}
    yield small_data

model_fits = {}
for data in get_data_range():
    if data['P'] >=20:
        continue
    print (data)
    
    try:
        model_fits[data['P']] = ps.stan(file='model.stan', data = data,iter = 10000)
    except:
        import sys
        print (sys.exc_info())
        break
